    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of an order of marine invertebrates having a flat, disk-shaped body, lacking the spherical symmetry of other echinoderms, but having five- or six-rayed markings on their surface; living on the sandy sea bottom of coastal North America south of the Arctic.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
